{
  "texts": [
    "These methods can be broadly classified into node clustering pooling, node drop pooling, and other pooling techniques based on how they coarsen a graph.",
    "This method retains nodes from the original graph by deleting nodes with lower significance scores using a learnable scoring function.",
    "It consists of three main modules:",
    "Score Generator: Calculates significance scores for each node in the input graph.",
    "Node Selector: Selects the top-k nodes with the highest significance scores."
  ]
}